  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6580.5 sitting below the 6601 flip line in PIN regime, dealers are currently net buying dips as they hedge their long gamma position, providing immediate support around the 6570 negative gamma wall where buying pressure intensifies. The massive positive gamma concentration at 6600 (50B+) creates a strong resistance ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell rallies, while the thick GEX walls between 6590-6595 should act as intermediate support levels. The recent GEX surge with extreme negative momentum (-63% over 5min) suggests dealers just absorbed significant flow, but the PIN regime structure should contain volatility and promote mean reversion back toward the 6590-6600 range.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to bounce off 6570 support and grind back up toward 6600 resistance in choppy fashion.",
